:: Hopeless Cycle
<<hopelessCycleStart>>
<<set _thermoDisable to true>><<effects>>
<<set Weather.set("heavyClouds", true, 600)>><<canvas-model-override "mouth" "neutral">>
<span class="narration">
It's generally agreed upon that the event took place late in the 14th century.
The Cloister of Virgo, as they called themselves, held much control over the region.
<br><br>

This comes some years after a religious conflict that nearly spelled their annihilation.
Persecution was common, as they were eager to punish any they deemed guilty of having a hand in the conflict.
Or their descendants.
</span>
<br><br>

It's rarely quiet in the temple's dungeon, but when it is, it's deafening.
<br><br>

One thing that never fails to inspire instant silence is the reverberation of heavy boots on stone.
There's only one pair of boots in the whole faith heavy enough to make that specific dirge,
and only one bastard big enough to wear them.
<br><br>

You lean forward in your plain wooden chair, counting the footsteps. Only one pair.
That means he's alone, and thus probably here to yell at you.
You put your book down and brace yourself as the light of his torch begins to leak into the guardhouse.
The other gaolers all stand at attention. You don't bother. It's never made a difference with him.
<br><br>

His massive frame finally comes into view, along with his ugly brown-bearded face, marred with a lopsided handprint branding. An absolute wall of a man. The Bishop's Hand. He's carrying something over his shoulder. A long, limp sack, split at the bottom into two-
no, that's a person. His dark eyes scan the room, passing each guard, until his eyes land on you. He holds his torch out wordlessly.
<br><br>

<<link [[Take the torch|Hopeless Cycle Torch]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Make him carry it himself|Hopeless Cycle Torch]]>><<hcSuspicion 2>><<set $phase to 2>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Offer to carry the new prisoner instead|Hopeless Cycle Torch]]>><<set $prisoner.love += 1>><<set $phase to 3>><</link>>
<br>

:: Hopeless Cycle Torch
<<set _thermoDisable to true>><<effects>>
<span class="narration">
There are many versions of this tale, but there are some constants across all of them.
The first of which is that the Bishop's Hand was a cruel, vicious enforcer.
<br><br>

Where the stories diverge depends on whether he was the exception, or the norm.
The wounds were still fresh. The Cloister's vengeance, swift and terrible. It inspired cruelty in many.
</span>
<br><br>

<<if $phase is 1>>
	<<wearProp "torch">>
	You take the outstretched torch, as is expected of you.
<<elseif $phase is 2>>
	You do nothing. He growls, before handing it out to someone else. He grabs your tunic and yanks you forward in front of him. Looks like you're not getting out of this one.
<<else>>
	<<wearProp "torch">>
	You outstretch your arms towards the prisoner. The Bishop's Hand makes an amused grunt, but hits you on the forehead with the handle of the torch, before holding it out again. You take the hint this time. <<pain 2>><<gpain>>
<</if>>
<br><br>

He nods towards the limp figure over his shoulder. "Fresh from the wall." His voice is a lecherous rumble, making the following belly laugh all the more unsettling. "Hounds enjoyed their meat."
He points forward, down the primary corridor. <<if $phase isnot 2>>You light the way forward.<<else>>The other guard lights the way forward, and you follow.<</if>>
<br><br>

One. Two. Three. Four. Five. Six. Seven. Eight. Nine. Ten. Nine. He stops to think. Eight. Nine. Ten. Nine. He finally stops on the ninth cell. Only five of the cells you passed were even occupied.
You expertly find the right key on your key ring, unlocking the cell. <<if $phase is 2>>He shoves you in ahead of him<<else>>You enter ahead of him<</if>>.
<br><br>

He approaches the back wall, laying the new prisoner down. "You won't get much noise out of this one," he says as he secures her silver manacles to the wall by a chain. "No more singing for this birdie."
<br><br>

He turns to you, chuckling. Staring. As if waiting for you to speak out of turn.
<br><br>

<<link [[Ask what her crimes are|Hopeless Cycle Ask]]>><<hcSuspicion 5>><<set $prisoner.love += 1>><<set $phase2 to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Stay silent|Hopeless Cycle Ask]]>><<set $phase2 to 2>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Ask what your orders are|Hopeless Cycle Ask]]>><<hcSuspicion -3>><<set $phase2 to 3>><</link>>
<br>

:: Hopeless Cycle Ask
<<set _thermoDisable to true>><<effects>>
<span class="narration">
Every spin on this tale, every divergence, comes from this man. Her personal gaoler.
His name is lost to time, but most sources point to him being a member of the old Fayne noble family.
A family with deep, historic ties to the cloister. It's probable that many of his brothers and sisters in worship were familial as well.
</span>
<br><br>

<<if $phase2 is 1>>
	You ask why she's being locked up. Immediately, he punches you in the gut, doubling you over. <<pain 6>><<ggpain>>
	<br><br>

	"You know better than to ask. You wait for me to tell you, if I think you need to know."
<<elseif $phase2 is 2>>
	You stay quiet. He makes a satisfied grunt.
<<else>>
	You obediently ask for your orders. He gruffs under his breath. "Such a good dog, always ready to heel."
<</if>>
<br><br>

He removes a pouch from his waist, and draws a big cross on the wall in dark grey paste. He speaks as he works.
<br><br>

"She's a witch. Consorted with the Dark Elk and seduced the townsfolk. They're not happy about her being taken." He walks to the next wall and starts the second cross. "Ungrateful pigs."
<br><br>

He finishes the cross, moving to the third wall. "She's your responsibility. Personally. Too much of a contamination risk for more than one guard, which means you don't touch any other prisoners." He pauses to point at you. <span class="blue">"It also means you get sanctified whenever you enter or leave the dungeon."</span>
<br><br>

He finishes the last cross. "<span class="red">Make sure she lives, but hates every minute of it.</span> Bring her salvation through suffering. <span class="blue">Be here every day, at mid-day, for her penance.</span> Keep her intact until the red moon. <span class="red">If you show mercy, I'll assume she bewitched you.</span>" He pushes past you, <<if $phase is 2>>leaving with the other guard<<else>><<handheldon>>yanking the torch from your hands and leaving the cell<</if>>. You're plunged into darkness.
<br><br>

The cell's too dark for you to even inspect her now. You'll need to grab another torch.
<br><br>

