:: Hopeless Cycle Prayer Report
<<set _thermoDisable to true>><<effects>>
<<hopelessCycleEffects>>
<span class="narration">The gaoler could not let the witch's defilement go unpunished. Justice was not something to be picked and chosen.</span>
<br><br>

You tell him that one of your brothers violated your prisoner. He tenses up.
<br><br>

You stand in deafening silence for a long time, before he finally stands.
<br><br>

"And how, brother, do you know that?"
<br><br>

You explain everything in excruciating detail. You're not even meaning to. The words flow from your mouth against your will.
<br><br>

He seems to get angrier with every word you say, until his shoulders finally fall. He smiles at you. Warmly. It makes you uncomfortable.
<br><br>

"It's hard to lie in a place so close to heaven. Good work, brother." He laughs, and pats you on the shoulder. "This presents a contamination risk. We will do an emergency inspection. Come." He leads you out of the prayer room, rings the confessional's bell loudly seven times, and walks with you to the cloister. <<hcSuspicion -50>><<hopelessCycleSus -3>>
<br><br>

<<link [[Next|Hopeless Cycle Prayer Report 2]]>><<pass 30>><</link>>
<br>

:: Hopeless Cycle Prayer Report 2
<<set _thermoDisable to true>><<effects>><<set $bus to "cloister">>
<<hopelessCycleEffects>>

Your brothers and sisters all line up in front of you and the Bishop's Hand in the cloister.
<br><br>

<<if Time.dayState is "night">>
	Many of them yawn, their posture slacking until the Hand's gaze falls upon them.
<<else>>
	They all stand at attention. Many look nervous.
<</if>>
<br><br>

The Hand whispers in your ear, asking for clarifying details. With each question, some of the crowd are permitted to leave, until there's only six monks left.
<br><br>

They're each given a chastity examination. Out of them, two fail. The Hand grabs them each by a shoulder, and looks back to you. "Are you certain it was only one?" They both look terrified.
<br><br>

<<link [[Yes|Hopeless Cycle Prayer Report 3]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[No|Hopeless Cycle Prayer Report 3]]>><<set $phase to 2>><</link>>
<br>

:: Hopeless Cycle Prayer Report 3
<<set _thermoDisable to true>><<effects>><<set $bus to "guardhouse">>
<<hopelessCycleEffects>>

<<if $phase is 1>>
	You nod your head.
<<else>>
	You shake your head.
<</if>>
The Hand huffs. "Then we have no choice." He starts to guide them both to the dungeon. You follow, along with an entire regiment of confessors.
<br><br>

You're led to <<print $prisoner.name>>'s cell. The hand walks in with both of the suspects. <<print $prisoner.name.toUpperFirst()>> looks up, shying away.
<br><br>

"Witch," the Hand spits. "One of the faithful has been tainted by your touch."
<br><br>

She blinks at him, not seeming to understand him. However, her eye falls upon the monk on the right. Her stare is pointedly hateful. That's enough indication for the Hand.
<br><br>

He shoves the other monk out of the cell, into the waiting arms of the confessors. "You must be purified," they say. He seems relieved to only be facing the normal punishment.
<br><br>

The guilty monk sneers, struggling in the Hand's grasp. "This is an outrage. I should not be punished for bringing this whore closer to God!" He's silenced as the Hand punches him directly in the face, sending him to the ground.
<br><br>

The Hand crouches, looking him in the eyes as he clutches his bleeding nose. "You have transgressed, brother. You have either given the witch what she needs to invite the Dark Elk... or have taken that taint into yourself, without sanction, and have become a contamination risk." He rips a pouch from his belt, and dumps powder on the ground in front of the door.
"You will be the vessel for that taint. You will purge. You will repent, and be forgiven." He nods to you, signaling for you to approach.
<br><br>

<<link [[Next|Hopeless Cycle Prayer Report 4]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Hopeless Cycle Prayer Report 4
<<set _thermoDisable to true>><<effects>>
<<hopelessCycleEffects>><<wearProp "whip" "khaki">>
<span class="narration">The witch was treated like a dog on a leash.</span>
<br><br>

The Hand holds out a silk cord for you to take. You grab it, wrapping it around <<print $prisoner.name>>'s neck. You've enacted this kind of punishment before. He then exits the cell, locking the door, but remains standing there. Watching.
<br><br>

You look at your prisoner. She eyes the monk angrily, her hands scraping against her shackles. The Hand licks his lips, and motions for you to unlock her shackles. You do so. She falls forwards, her hands digging into the stone as her grey eye pierces through the monk.
<br><br>

He tries to stand. In one swift motion, you unclasp your whip and lash him in the leg. He tumbles back down, and you give him a second lash for good measure.
<br><br>

He pushes himself back against the wall. "P-please, your grace, have mercy!"
<br><br>

The Hand laughs. "I'm not the one you should be asking." <<print $prisoner.name.toUpperFirst()>> drags herself forwards. You walk forwards with her.
<br><br>

The monk, the rapist, the defiler, the oathbreaker looks to you, pleading. Your fist clenches around the cord.
<br><br>

She nearly reaches him, her left arm and hand becoming black. Her fingers elongating, sharpening. The antler on her head pulsing.
<br><br>

<<link [[Show mercy|Hopeless Cycle Prayer Report 5]]>><<handheldon>><<set $phase to 1>><<pass 15>><</link>>
<br>
<<if $sadism_level gte 2 and ($prisoner.love gte 45 or $prisoner.love gte 30 and $prisonerEvents.includes("comfort"))>>
